---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto py-8 px-4">
    <!-- Heading and Intro Text -->
    <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Class</h2>
    <p class="text-lg mb-8 text-gray-200">
      Their background.
    </p>
    
    <!-- Region Grid -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      
      <!-- Region Card 1: Aeolian Archipelago -->
      <article class="flex flex-col bg-gray-800 rounded shadow overflow-hidden">
        <img
          src="/images/karkorte/kraken.png"
          alt="Kraken"
          class="w-full object-cover h-48 md:h-60"
        />
        <div class="p-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Scavenger</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
            Scavengers are an essential part of the city of Karkorte as they help to maintain the infrastructure of the city. 
            Due to the constant pressure of monster attacks on the city, more materials are needed in order to keep the city habitable.
          </p>
          <a href="https://tidesofchange.github.io/docs/species/mutated-humans/" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 hover:underline">
            Read More
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
      
      <!-- Region Card 2: Lumea -->
      <article class="flex flex-col bg-gray-800 rounded shadow overflow-hidden">
        <img
          src="/images/karkorte/moby.png"
          alt="Moby"
          class="w-full object-cover h-48 md:h-60"
        />
        <div class="p-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Hunter</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
            Hunters are also backbones of Karkote due to the low amounts of food present at a time. 
            There is no infrastructure set up for farming, so Karkorte is mainly supported by hunting and gathering. 
          </p>
          <a href="https://tidesofchange.github.io/TRPG/species/mutated-humans/" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 hover:underline">
            Read More
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
      
      <!-- Region Card 3: Karkote -->
      <article class="flex flex-col bg-gray-800 rounded shadow overflow-hidden">
        <img
          src="/images/archipelago/seed.jpg"
          alt="Woodland"
          class="w-full object-cover h-48 md:h-60"
        />
        <div class="p-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Seed Keeper</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
            Seed Keepers are a group of scholars that take care of the seeds in the Seed Vault. 
            They are responsible for cataloging, studying, and protecting the seeds.

          </p>
          <a href="https://tidesofchange.github.io/TRPG/species/woodland-creatures/" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 hover:underline">
            Read More
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
      
      <!-- Region Card 4: Grønn Verden -->
      <article class="flex flex-col bg-gray-800 rounded shadow overflow-hidden">
        <img
          src="/images/archipelago/farmer.jpg"
          alt="Ectopian"
          class="w-full object-cover h-48 md:h-60"
        />
        <div class="p-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Farmer</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
            The last generation of Farmers that actually worked with the seeds in the Seed Vault weren’t capable of fighting and thought that their skill set was better put towards helping their communities. They do a little bit of everything to help out and make their communities better, whether that be building new homes, making repairs, or farming to ensure everyone has enough food.
          </p>
          <a href="https://tidesofchange.github.io/TRPG/species/ecotopians/" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 hover:underline">
            Read More
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
      
      <!-- Region Card 5: Sylvangrove -->
      <article class="flex flex-col bg-gray-800 rounded shadow overflow-hidden">
        <img
          src="/images/archipelago/aqualumean.png"
          alt="AquaLumean"
          class="w-full object-cover h-48 md:h-60"
        />
        <div class="p-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Ecotechnician</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
            Sustainable engineers that harness the potential of synergizing technology with nature. Ecotechnics as a discipline traces its origin to the late stages of pre-apocalyptic Earth when people began to realize that reliance on technology or the natural environment in isolation would not be enough for their survival.
          </p>
          <a href="https://tidesofchange.github.io/TRPG/species/aqualumeans/" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 hover:underline">
            Read More
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="flex flex-col bg-gray-800 rounded shadow overflow-hidden">
        <img
          src="/images/archipelago/aqualumean.png"
          alt="Atlantean"
          class="w-full object-cover h-48 md:h-60"
        />
        <div class="p-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Public Servant</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
            Civically minded diplomats who jump at the opportunity to lead people. 
            Every era of the Earth has seen these types of people in some form or another, and the current one is no different. 
          </p>
          <a href="https://tidesofchange.github.io/TRPG/species/lumea-humans/" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 hover:underline">
            Read More
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>


      <article class="flex flex-col bg-gray-800 rounded shadow overflow-hidden">
        <img
          src="/images/archipelago/parrot.jpg"
          alt="Atlantean"
          class="w-full object-cover h-48 md:h-60"
        />
        <div class="p-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Ranger</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
            The ranger grew up in a close knit village that valued community over anything. 
            The rangers father was an explorer and the mother was a warrior. 
          </p>
          <a href="https://tidesofchange.github.io/TRPG/species/bird-pirates/" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 hover:underline">
            Read More
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>


      <article class="flex flex-col bg-gray-800 rounded shadow overflow-hidden">
        <img
          src="/images/archipelago/parrot.jpg"
          alt="Atlantean"
          class="w-full object-cover h-48 md:h-60"
        />
        <div class="p-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Enchanter</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
            The enchanter did so and found that The Enchanters Code was now a full book, not a container anymore. 
            Ever since this experience, the enchanter has been working on their magic. 
          </p>
          <a href="https://tidesofchange.github.io/TRPG/species/bird-pirates/" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 hover:underline">
            Read More
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>


      <article class="flex flex-col bg-gray-800 rounded shadow overflow-hidden">
        <img
          src="/images/archipelago/cloudrunner.jpg"
          alt="Atlantean"
          class="w-full object-cover h-48 md:h-60"
        />
        <div class="p-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Cloudrunner</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
            Cloudrunners are criminals. Although some may have noble intentions or lofty goals, the life of a Cloudrunner is characterized by violent conflict, constant danger, and a struggle for survival.  
          </p>
          <a href="https://tidesofchange.github.io/TRPG/species/bird-pirates/" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 hover:underline">
            Read More
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="flex flex-col bg-gray-800 rounded shadow overflow-hidden">
        <img
          src="/images/archipelago/skycaller.png"
          alt="Atlantean"
          class="w-full object-cover h-48 md:h-60"
        />
        <div class="p-4">
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">Skycaller</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">
            Both feared and hallowed amongst the residents of Aeolian Archipelago, the name “Skycaller” invokes omens of both awe and terror. Skycallers are exceptionally rare weather shamans capable of taming the storms that ravage the Archipelago, and are both feared and respected amongst all. 
          </p>
          <a href="https://tidesofchange.github.io/TRPG/species/bird-pirates/" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 hover:underline">
            Read More
          </a>
        </div>
      </article>
      
      
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>